#📦009-eco-mascot @Andy | Eco @Hen | Eco  @Bryce  | Eco @Dave | Eco @Henry  |  Eco 

On the first AMA "State of the Discord" there was a question:      

«What is the durable competitive advantage of ECO in comparison to existing or future competitors?»  

Andy Bromberg answered it: 

«If we’re talking about the ECO app here, the reality is that our product is structured and our business is structured in a way that we want to give all the benefits back to the users.»

In ancient Greek mythology, Prometheus acts as the protector of people.

When Zeus decided to establish a new world order, he singled out the people in the lowest place. Zeus is at the top, and the humans are at the bottom. Zeus wanted to take everything from people.

Prometheus understood that without fire, people would very quickly return to the wild times. Prometheus stole the fire to give it to the people. Coming to Olympus in the simple clothes of a traveler, he approached the divine fire. When they stopped paying attention to him, he quickly and carefully placed the embers inside the staff.

Unnoticed, Prometheus descended to the ground and swept like a whirlwind through the places where people lived, distributing embers everywhere. And the dark night was lit up with bright sparks of home fires and light.

Prometheus brought fire back to the people! 🔥 

I believe that the ECO philosophy is similar to the Prometheus philosophy. ECO also wants to return to people the fire, light, and energy that the banks took away. Only instead of a staff, ECO puts fire in its mobile app. :eco_heart: 

In this concept, I depicted the "Digital Prometheus" as 50% human (with a human face), and 50% digital technology, because it looks like ECO.

The ECO mobile app is also created with a human face. It is convenient, simple and understandable to everyone. But at the same time, powerful digital technologies are hidden under the hood of ECO.
Digital Prometheus can be drawn in any style, angle, and colors. Evaluate the concept idea.
